National days like Jamhuri should be occasions for soul-searching and stock-taking.  Folks who were born in December 1963 are now grandparents. Most of them are looking forward to retirement from their jobs — if they still have any during these troubled times.
They are as old as Independent Kenya itself and they have, without fail, been celebrating Jamhuri Day since 1964. In short, this country has come of age, but it is fast sliding towards premature senescence.



