Despite remonstrating that I am neither a mdosi from Nairobi nor do I, ordinarily, hobnob with presidents over anything at all, they were not convinced and I had to part with Sh200 so they could buy mugfuls of stronger stuff than tea to mollify them.
This means that the much-hyped development has never trickled down to the very poor and they don’t see why they should be excited about national days or stuff like the Building Bridges Initiative, which they hardly understand.
